<subSubSection pageId="66" pageNumber="67" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="66.[151,1436,934,1828]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1732,1756]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
Distant’s manuscript name “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" authorityYear="2011" box="[646,750,1732,1756]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Igerna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="delineata">
<emphasis box="[646,750,1732,1756]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">delineata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” (on the specimen) is retained for this species. This species resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[270,417,1769,1792]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Igerna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atrovenosa">
<emphasis box="[270,417,1769,1792]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">I. atrovenosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" authorityYear="2011" box="[473,574,1769,1792]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Igerna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurora">
<emphasis box="[473,574,1769,1792]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">I. aurora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It can be easily distinguished by the aedeagus being more arcuate and sunk into the base of dorsal apodeme and by the caudodorsal lobe-like extention of the male pygofer.
</paragraph>
